{{Distinguish|Aaron (Jaredite)|Aaron (Nephite)}}
{{about|the Lamanite figure in the Book of Mormon||Aaron (disambiguation)}}
{{Religious text primary|date=October 2011}}
{{Portal|Book of Mormon}}

According to the [[Book of Mormon]], '''Aaron''' was a [[Lamanite]] [[king]] who lived during the 4th century in the [[Americas]].  He is mentioned in [[Book of Mormon (Mormon's record)|Mormon's record]] as a man who led 44,000 Lamanites to battle against [[Mormon (prophet)|Mormon]]'s [[Nephite]] army of 42,000.<ref>{{lds|Mormon|mormon|2|9}}</ref>  Mormon's army prevailed in the battle, although ultimately the Nephite armies were conclusively defeated, which marked the end of their civilization.  Mormon described the armies of Aaron as exercising "awful brutality".<ref>{{lds|Mormon|mormon|9|17}}</ref>

