==Book of Mormon Movie==
In ''[[The Book of Mormon Movie, Vol. 1: The Journey]]'', adapted from First and Second Nephi, Laman was portrayed by Mark Gollaher and Lemuel by Cragun Foulger. The portrayals were highly influenced by [[Arnold Friberg]] paintings of the characters.

The film was widely panned by Mormon<ref>[http://www.deseretnews.com/article/700003321/Book-of-Mormon-Movie-Volume-1-The-Journey-The.html The Book of Mormon Movie], Deseret News</ref> and non-Mormon critics.<ref>[http://www.austinchronicle.com/calendar/film/2004-03-05/199711/ The Book of Mormon Movie, Volume 1: The Journey] in the Austin Chronicle</ref>. The Austin Chronicle wrote of "''sinister siblings Laman and Lemuel (Gollaher, Foulger) running rampant with Stone Age stilettos and waywardness like some Hebraic version of the [[Bowery Boys]]’ [[Leo Gorcey]] and [[Huntz Hall]]''"

